Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with distributional semantic models and their performance over multiple languages, which falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of machine translation and its impact on the performance of semantic relatedness models can be considered as an application of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques such as Word2Vec and machine translation to improve the performance of semantic relatedness models. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - Semantic relatedness is an important aspect of information retrieval, and this paper provides insights into the performance of multilingual semantic relatedness models. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - While this sub-category may not seem immediately relevant, the impact of machine translation on cross-lingual communication and understanding can have societal implications.
